For each (i,j), compute check, and if ch>0, print the line. The check function:

def check(n, x, y, h, cx, cy):

    ch = -1

    for each point where h[i]>0:

        compute ch as |x[i]-cx| + |y[i]-cy| + h[i]

        break (so take the first h[i]>0's value?)

    then check for all points:

        h[i] must equal max( ch - (distance), 0 )

    if all pass, return ch, else -1. Wait, in the code: In check:

